<item>
            <title>[HBASE-2292] Need to be able to specify a custom RowLock for incrementColumnValue </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2292</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m grabbing my own &lt;tt&gt;RowLock&lt;/tt&gt; on a given row and then I want to do an ICV on the row (among other things) while I hold the lock.  Unlike &lt;tt&gt;Get&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;Put&lt;/tt&gt; and whatnot, there&apos;s no way to specify your own &lt;tt&gt;RowLock&lt;/tt&gt; when doing an ICV.  Technically, you can live without this since you can get just a &lt;tt&gt;Get&lt;/tt&gt; followed by a &lt;tt&gt;Put&lt;/tt&gt; after having manually incremented the value, which is guaranteed to work as you hold the &lt;tt&gt;RowLock&lt;/tt&gt; on that row, but it would be nice to be able to just do an ICV.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Right now, &lt;tt&gt;incrementColumnValue&lt;/tt&gt; attempts to lock the row again (which is normal), thus causing my client to &quot;deadlock&quot; itself until its &lt;tt&gt;RowLock&lt;/tt&gt;&apos;s lease expires.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
